{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a garbage man."},{"time":3000,"text":"And you might find it interesting that I became a garbage man,"},{"time":6000,"text":"because I absolutely hate waste."},{"time":8000,"text":"I hope, within the next 10 minutes,"},{"time":11000,"text":"to change the way you think"},{"time":13000,"text":"about a lot of the stuff in your life."},{"time":15000,"text":"And I'd like to start at the very beginning."},{"time":17000,"text":"Think back when you were just a kid."},{"time":19000,"text":"How did look at the stuff in your life?"},{"time":21000,"text":"Perhaps it was like these toddler rules:"},{"time":25000,"text":"It's my stuff if I saw it first."},{"time":28000,"text":"The entire pile is my stuff if I'm building something."},{"time":32000,"text":"The more stuff that's mine, the better."},{"time":35000,"text":"And of course, it's your stuff if it's broken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":40000,"text":"Well after spending about 20 years in the recycling industry,"},{"time":42000,"text":"it's become pretty clear to me"},{"time":44000,"text":"that we don't necessarily leave these toddler rules behind"},{"time":46000,"text":"as we develop into adults."},{"time":48000,"text":"And let me tell you why I have that perspective."},{"time":50000,"text":"Because each and every day"},{"time":52000,"text":"at our recycling plants around the world"},{"time":54000,"text":"we handle about one million pounds"},{"time":57000,"text":"of people's discarded stuff."},{"time":59000,"text":"Now a million pounds a day sounds like a lot of stuff,"},{"time":61000,"text":"but it's a tiny drop of the durable goods"},{"time":64000,"text":"that are disposed each and every year around the world --"},{"time":66000,"text":"well less than one percent."},{"time":68000,"text":"In fact, the United Nations estimates"},{"time":70000,"text":"that there's about 85 billion pounds a year"},{"time":72000,"text":"of electronics waste"},{"time":74000,"text":"that gets discarded around the world each and every year --"},{"time":76000,"text":"and that's one of the most rapidly growing parts of our waste stream."},{"time":79000,"text":"And if you throw in other durable goods like automobiles and so forth,"},{"time":82000,"text":"that number well more than doubles."},{"time":84000,"text":"And of course, the more developed the country,"},{"time":86000,"text":"the bigger these mountains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88000,"text":"Now when you see these mountains,"},{"time":90000,"text":"most people think of garbage."},{"time":92000,"text":"We see above-ground mines."},{"time":94000,"text":"And the reason we see mines is because there's a lot of valuable raw materials"},{"time":97000,"text":"that went into making all of this stuff in the first place."},{"time":100000,"text":"And it's becoming increasingly important"},{"time":102000,"text":"that we figure out how to extract these raw materials"},{"time":105000,"text":"from these extremely complicated waste streams."},{"time":108000,"text":"Because as we've heard all week at TED,"},{"time":110000,"text":"the world's getting to be a smaller place with more people in it"},{"time":113000,"text":"who want more and more stuff."},{"time":115000,"text":"And of course, they want the toys and the tools"},{"time":118000,"text":"that many of us take for granted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"And what goes into making those toys and tools"},{"time":123000,"text":"that we use every single day?"},{"time":125000,"text":"It's mostly many types of plastics and many types of metals."},{"time":128000,"text":"And the metals, we typically get"},{"time":131000,"text":"from ore that we mine"},{"time":133000,"text":"in ever widening mines"},{"time":135000,"text":"and ever deepening mines around the world."},{"time":137000,"text":"And the plastics, we get from oil,"},{"time":140000,"text":"which we go to more remote locations"},{"time":142000,"text":"and drill ever deeper wells to extract."},{"time":145000,"text":"And these practices have"},{"time":147000,"text":"significant economic and environmental implications"},{"time":150000,"text":"that we're already starting to see today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"The good news is we are starting to recover materials from our end-of-life stuff"},{"time":156000,"text":"and starting to recycle our end-of-life stuff,"},{"time":158000,"text":"particularly in regions of the world like here in Europe"},{"time":161000,"text":"that have recycling policies in place"},{"time":164000,"text":"that require that this stuff be recycled"},{"time":166000,"text":"in a responsible manner."},{"time":168000,"text":"Most of what's extracted from our end-of-life stuff,"},{"time":170000,"text":"if it makes it to a recycler, are the metals."},{"time":173000,"text":"To put that in perspective --"},{"time":175000,"text":"and I'm using steel as a proxy here for metals,"},{"time":177000,"text":"because it's the most common metal --"},{"time":179000,"text":"if your stuff makes it to a recycler,"},{"time":181000,"text":"probably over 90 percent of the metals"},{"time":183000,"text":"are going to be recovered and reused for another purpose."},{"time":186000,"text":"Plastics are a whole other story:"},{"time":188000,"text":"well less than 10 percent are recovered."},{"time":190000,"text":"In fact, it's more like five percent."},{"time":192000,"text":"Most of it's incinerated or landfilled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194000,"text":"Now most people think that's because plastics are a throw-away material,"},{"time":196000,"text":"have very little value."},{"time":198000,"text":"But actually, plastics are several times more valuable than steel."},{"time":201000,"text":"And there's more plastics produced and consumed"},{"time":203000,"text":"around the world on a volume basis"},{"time":205000,"text":"every year than steel."},{"time":207000,"text":"So why is such a plentiful and valuable material"},{"time":210000,"text":"not recovered at anywhere near the rate"},{"time":212000,"text":"of the less valuable material?"},{"time":214000,"text":"Well it's predominantly because"},{"time":216000,"text":"metals are very easy to recycle"},{"time":218000,"text":"from other materials and from one another."},{"time":220000,"text":"They have very different densities."},{"time":222000,"text":"They have different electrical and magnetic properties."},{"time":224000,"text":"And they even have different colors."},{"time":226000,"text":"So it's very easy for either humans or machines"},{"time":229000,"text":"to separate these metals"},{"time":231000,"text":"from one another and from other materials."},{"time":233000,"text":"Plastics have overlapping densities over a very narrow range."},{"time":237000,"text":"They have either identical or very similar"},{"time":239000,"text":"electrical and magnetic properties."},{"time":241000,"text":"And any plastic can be any color,"},{"time":243000,"text":"as you probably well know."},{"time":245000,"text":"So the traditional ways of separating materials"},{"time":247000,"text":"just simply don't work for plastics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"Another consequence of metals being so easy to recycle by humans"},{"time":254000,"text":"is that a lot of our stuff from the developed world --"},{"time":257000,"text":"and sadly to say, particularly from the United States,"},{"time":260000,"text":"where we don't have any recycling policies in place like here in Europe --"},{"time":263000,"text":"finds its way to developing countries"},{"time":265000,"text":"for low-cost recycling."},{"time":268000,"text":"People, for as little as a dollar a day, pick through our stuff."},{"time":271000,"text":"They extract what they can, which is mostly the metals --"},{"time":273000,"text":"circuit boards and so forth --"},{"time":275000,"text":"and they leave behind mostly what they can't recover,"},{"time":277000,"text":"which is, again, mostly the plastics."},{"time":280000,"text":"Or they burn the plastics to get to the metals"},{"time":283000,"text":"in burn houses like you see here."},{"time":285000,"text":"And they extract the metals by hand."},{"time":289000,"text":"Now while this may be the low-economic-cost solution,"},{"time":292000,"text":"this is certainly not the low-environmental"},{"time":294000,"text":"or human health-and-safety solution."},{"time":297000,"text":"I call this environmental arbitrage."},{"time":300000,"text":"And it's not fair, it's not safe"},{"time":303000,"text":"and it's not sustainable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"Now because the plastics are so plentiful --"},{"time":308000,"text":"and by the way,"},{"time":310000,"text":"those other methods don't lead to the recovery of plastics, obviously --"},{"time":312000,"text":"but people do try to recover the plastics."},{"time":314000,"text":"This is just one example."},{"time":316000,"text":"This is a photo I took standing on the rooftops"},{"time":318000,"text":"of one of the largest slums in the world in Mumbai, India."},{"time":321000,"text":"They store the plastics on the roofs."},{"time":323000,"text":"They bring them below those roofs into small workshops like these,"},{"time":326000,"text":"and people try very hard to separate the plastics,"},{"time":329000,"text":"by color, by shape, by feel,"},{"time":331000,"text":"by any technique they can."},{"time":333000,"text":"And sometimes they'll resort to what's known as the \"burn and sniff\" technique"},{"time":335000,"text":"where they'll burn the plastic and smell the fumes"},{"time":337000,"text":"to try to determine the type of plastic."},{"time":340000,"text":"None of these techniques result in any amount of recycling"},{"time":343000,"text":"in any significant way."},{"time":345000,"text":"And by the way,"},{"time":347000,"text":"please don't try this technique at home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349000,"text":"So what are we to do about this space-age material,"},{"time":352000,"text":"at least what we used to call a space-aged material, these plastics?"},{"time":355000,"text":"Well I certainly believe that it's far too valuable and far too abundant"},{"time":358000,"text":"to keep putting back in the ground"},{"time":360000,"text":"or certainly send up in smoke."},{"time":362000,"text":"So about 20 years ago, I literally started in my garage tinkering around,"},{"time":365000,"text":"trying to figure out how to separate"},{"time":367000,"text":"these very similar materials from each other,"},{"time":369000,"text":"and eventually enlisted a lot of my friends,"},{"time":372000,"text":"in the mining world actually, and in the plastics world,"},{"time":375000,"text":"and we started going around to mining laboratories around the world."},{"time":378000,"text":"Because after all, we're doing above-ground mining."},{"time":381000,"text":"And we eventually broke the code."},{"time":383000,"text":"This is the last frontier of recycling."},{"time":385000,"text":"It's the last major material"},{"time":387000,"text":"to be recovered in any significant amount on the Earth."},{"time":389000,"text":"And we finally figured out how to do it."},{"time":391000,"text":"And in the process, we started recreating"},{"time":393000,"text":"how the plastics industry makes plastics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395000,"text":"The traditional way to make plastics"},{"time":397000,"text":"is with oil or petrochemicals."},{"time":399000,"text":"You breakdown the molecules, you recombine them in very specific ways,"},{"time":402000,"text":"to make all the wonderful plastics that we enjoy each and every day."},{"time":405000,"text":"We said, there's got to be a more sustainable way to make plastics."},{"time":408000,"text":"And not just sustainable from an environmental standpoint,"},{"time":411000,"text":"sustainable from an economic standpoint as well."},{"time":414000,"text":"Well a good place to start is with waste."},{"time":416000,"text":"It certainly doesn't cost as much as oil,"},{"time":418000,"text":"and it's plentiful,"},{"time":420000,"text":"as I hope that you've been able to see from the photographs."},{"time":422000,"text":"And because we're not breaking down the plastic into molecules"},{"time":424000,"text":"and recombining them,"},{"time":426000,"text":"we're using a mining approach to extract the materials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"We have significantly lower capital costs"},{"time":431000,"text":"in our plant equipment."},{"time":433000,"text":"We have enormous energy savings."},{"time":435000,"text":"I don't know how many other projects on the planet right now"},{"time":437000,"text":"can save 80 to 90 percent of the energy"},{"time":440000,"text":"compared to making something the traditional way."},{"time":442000,"text":"And instead of plopping down several hundred million dollars"},{"time":444000,"text":"to build a chemical plant"},{"time":446000,"text":"that will only make one type of plastic for its entire life,"},{"time":449000,"text":"our plants can make any type of plastic we feed them."},{"time":452000,"text":"And we make a drop-in replacement"},{"time":454000,"text":"for that plastic that's made from petrochemicals."},{"time":456000,"text":"Our customers get to enjoy"},{"time":458000,"text":"huge CO2 savings."},{"time":460000,"text":"They get to close the loop with their products."},{"time":462000,"text":"And they get to make more sustainable products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"In the short time period I have,"},{"time":466000,"text":"I want to show you a little bit of a sense about how we do this."},{"time":469000,"text":"It starts with metal recyclers who shred our stuff into very small bits."},{"time":472000,"text":"They recover the metals"},{"time":474000,"text":"and leave behind what's called shredder residue -- it's their waste --"},{"time":476000,"text":"a very complex mixture of materials,"},{"time":478000,"text":"but predominantly plastics."},{"time":480000,"text":"We take out the things that aren't plastics,"},{"time":482000,"text":"such as the metals they missed, carpeting, foam, rubber,"},{"time":485000,"text":"wood, glass, paper, you name it."},{"time":488000,"text":"Even an occasional dead animal, unfortunately."},{"time":490000,"text":"And it goes in the first part of our process here, which is more like traditional recycling."},{"time":493000,"text":"We're sieving the material, we're using magnets,"},{"time":495000,"text":"we're using air classification."},{"time":497000,"text":"It looks like the Willy Wonka factory at this point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499000,"text":"At the end of this process, we have a mixed plastic composite:"},{"time":502000,"text":"many different types of plastics"},{"time":504000,"text":"and many different grades of plastics."},{"time":506000,"text":"This goes into the more sophisticated part of our process,"},{"time":508000,"text":"and the really hard work, multi-step separation process begins."},{"time":512000,"text":"We grind the plastic down to about the size of your small fingernail."},{"time":515000,"text":"We use a very highly automated process"},{"time":517000,"text":"to sort those plastics,"},{"time":519000,"text":"not only by type, but by grade."},{"time":521000,"text":"And out the end of that part of the process"},{"time":523000,"text":"come little flakes of plastic:"},{"time":525000,"text":"one type, one grade."},{"time":527000,"text":"We then use optical sorting to color sort this material."},{"time":530000,"text":"We blend it in 50,000-lb. blending silos."},{"time":533000,"text":"We push that material to extruders where we melt it,"},{"time":536000,"text":"push it through small die holes,"},{"time":538000,"text":"make spaghetti-like plastic strands."},{"time":540000,"text":"And we chop those strands"},{"time":542000,"text":"into what are called pellets."},{"time":544000,"text":"And this becomes the currency of the plastics industry."},{"time":548000,"text":"This is the same material"},{"time":551000,"text":"that you would get from oil."},{"time":553000,"text":"And today,"},{"time":555000,"text":"we're producing it from your old stuff,"},{"time":558000,"text":"and it's going right back into your new stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"So now, instead of your stuff ending up"},{"time":572000,"text":"on a hillside in a developing country"},{"time":574000,"text":"or literally going up in smoke,"},{"time":576000,"text":"you can find your old stuff"},{"time":578000,"text":"back on top of your desk in new products,"},{"time":581000,"text":"in your office,"},{"time":583000,"text":"or back at work in your home."},{"time":585000,"text":"And these are just a few examples"},{"time":587000,"text":"of companies that are buying our plastic,"},{"time":589000,"text":"replacing virgin plastic,"},{"time":591000,"text":"to make their new products."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593000,"text":"So I hope I've changed the way you look at"},{"time":595000,"text":"at least some of the stuff in your life."},{"time":597000,"text":"We took our clues from mother nature."},{"time":599000,"text":"Mother nature wastes very little,"},{"time":601000,"text":"reuses practically everything."},{"time":603000,"text":"And I hope that you stop looking at yourself as a consumer --"},{"time":606000,"text":"that's a label I've always hated my entire life --"},{"time":609000,"text":"and think of yourself as just using resources in one form,"},{"time":613000,"text":"until they can be transformed to another form"},{"time":615000,"text":"for another use later in time."},{"time":617000,"text":"And finally, I hope you agree with me"},{"time":620000,"text":"to change that last toddler rule just a little bit"},{"time":623000,"text":"to: \"If it's broken, it's my stuff.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":626000,"text":"Thank you for your time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}